title: Essays, First Series (version 2)
creator: Ralph Waldo Emerson
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description: LibriVox recording of Essays, First Series, by Ralph Waldo Emerson. Read by Bob Neufeld. Essays, First Series is a series of 12 essays written by Ralph Waldo Emerson concerning transcendentalism, including Self-Reliance. It was published in 1841. (Summary by Wikipedia) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
